From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mark Harfouche <mark.harfouche@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 17 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] python: make the generated cv2 loader relocatable

OpenCV ships a small python loader (cv2/__init__.py + cv2/config.py +
cv2/config-3.py) that locates the compiled extension (cv2/python-3/
cv2.abi3.so) and the native OpenCV shared libraries at import time.

The paths written into config.py / config-3.py are LOADER_DIR-relative
only when OPENCV_PYTHON_INSTALL_PATH is a *relative* path. When it is
absolute -- which is the default for essentially every packaging system,
since OPENCV_PYTHON_INSTALL_PATH falls back to the absolute
PYTHON3_PACKAGES_PATH -- modules/python/python_loader.cmake and
modules/python/common.cmake instead bake the build-time absolute
CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX into the loader. That absolute path:

  * does not survive relocation of the install tree, and
  * for stable ABI (PYTHON3_LIMITED_API / abi3) builds hard-codes the
    build interpreter's "lib/pythonX.Y/site-packages" into the loader, so
    the single build that is meant to run on every later python points at
    a site-packages directory that does not exist in those environments.

Downstream packagers work around this by passing a hand-computed relative
OPENCV_PYTHON3_INSTALL_PATH. Make OpenCV do the right thing itself: if the
resolved install path is absolute but lives inside CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX,
rewrite it relative to the prefix before the loader is generated, so the
loader uses os.path.join(LOADER_DIR, ...) paths. The relative offset is a
function of the install *depth*, which is identical for every python
version, so a single abi3 build relocates correctly across pythons.

Install paths that fall outside CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX (e.g. a fixed system
site-packages, or layouts where site-packages and the libraries live under
separate prefixes) are left untouched, preserving the previous behaviour.
---
 modules/python/common.cmake | 19 +++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 19 insertions(+)

diff --git a/modules/python/common.cmake b/modules/python/common.cmake
index e9375af..aaded46 100644
--- a/modules/python/common.cmake
+++ b/modules/python/common.cmake
@@ -165,6 +165,25 @@ if(NOT " ${PYTHON}" STREQUAL " PYTHON"
     set(OPENCV_PYTHON_INSTALL_PATH "${${PYTHON}_PACKAGES_PATH}")
   endif()
 endif()
+# conda-forge: make the generated cv2 python loader relocatable.
+# OpenCV writes cv2/config.py and cv2/config-3.py with paths that locate the
+# compiled extension and the native OpenCV libraries relative to the install
+# prefix. When OPENCV_PYTHON_INSTALL_PATH is absolute, those paths are baked as
+# the build-time absolute prefix; the loader then breaks once the package is
+# relocated, and -- for stable ABI (abi3) builds -- once the single build is
+# installed into a different python than the one it was built with. If the
+# install path lives inside CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX, rewrite it relative to the
+# prefix so the loader emits os.path.join(LOADER_DIR, ...) paths instead. Install
+# paths outside the prefix (e.g. a system site-packages) are left untouched.
+if(DEFINED OPENCV_PYTHON_INSTALL_PATH AND IS_ABSOLUTE "${OPENCV_PYTHON_INSTALL_PATH}")
+  file(RELATIVE_PATH __ocv_python_install_path_rel
+       "${CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX}" "${OPENCV_PYTHON_INSTALL_PATH}")
+  if(NOT __ocv_python_install_path_rel STREQUAL ""
+      AND NOT __ocv_python_install_path_rel MATCHES "^\\.\\.")
+    set(OPENCV_PYTHON_INSTALL_PATH "${__ocv_python_install_path_rel}")
+  endif()
+  unset(__ocv_python_install_path_rel)
+endif()

 if(NOT OPENCV_SKIP_PYTHON_LOADER AND DEFINED OPENCV_PYTHON_INSTALL_PATH)
   include("${CMAKE_CURRENT_LIST_DIR}/python_loader.cmake")
--
